To support our young Soviet Republic, it is vital to get the people to accept our ideas. To this end, an unprecedented propaganda campaign should be launched among Soviet citizens. "Proletarians of all countries, unite!", "The Party is the mind, honor and conscience of our epoch!", "The people and the Party are one!", "Soviet means great!" So ... Our goals are clear, the tasks are defined - for work, comrades!

In economic science, the term "expropriation" is understood as the deprivation of property and social status by one social stratum or class of another stratum or class. In our country, the recently formed Soviet government was one of its first decisions to issue a decree "On expropriation." It means the forcible withdrawal of all means of production from private property, including land, and transferring them to state property. The government assigned the responsibility for the implementation of the decree to the new law enforcement agencies, and also called on all conscientious citizens to join the acts of expropriation. In practice, this resulted in the pogroms of most shops, restaurants, banks and other establishments owned by one or another entrepreneur. People in expensive clothes were attacked and checked both by citizens and by law enforcement officers. Many of those who resisted were shot on the spot. The number of victims is not known exactly. All factories and production facilities were transferred to workers' self-government. All over the world, criticism is heard against our government, but it is adamant in its will to build socialism and has already declared that it will stop at nothing.

The victory of the left bloc in the last elections made it possible to carry out radical transformations in the political and economic systems of the country. However, in spite of the fact that the left forces have received huge scope for implementing their program, there is still resistance from the liberal opposition. The success of all further transformations now depends on whether the communists and socialists can come to an agreement.

Gradually strengthening their positions, the communists achieved complete dominance in the Soviets. Now that neither the liberals, nor the other leftists any longer pose any danger to the regime, the Communist Party can begin implementing its extensive program of rebuilding the world.

With the victory of the liberal bloc in the last parliamentary elections, noticeable changes in the style of the country's leadership began to be felt. State control in the economy was weakened, and censorship in print media gradually disappeared. Finally, the time has come to officially declare - we are a democratic rule of law with a republican form of government!

The reshuffle in the Central Committee of our Communist Party led to the victory of the liberal faction and the subsequent series of political and economic reforms. Finally, the party leadership announced the proclamation of a democratic republic.
